Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_ptn_fplan_mode(25.10)                            get_ptn_fplan_mode(25.10)

Name
       get_ptn_fplan_mode  - Retrieves information about the option values set
       using the set_ptn_fplan_mode command

Syntax
        get_ptn_fplan_mode

       [-help]

       [-export]

       [-import]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Retrieves  information  about  the  option   values   set   using   the
       set_ptn_fplan_mode command.

Parameters
       -export
              Retrieves  the  value  of  data  that  saveParititon -fplan will
              write. An empty list means default objects are written.

              Default: special_route (default data + special route  is  always
              saved)

              Data_type: enums={macro special_route pin_constraint}_list

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each get_ptn_fplan_mode parameter.

               For a detailed description of the command and all of its  para-
              meters, use the man command:

              man get_ptn_fplan_mode

       -import
              Retrieves  the  value  of  data  that assembleDesign -fplan will
              bring back. An empty list  means  default  objects  are  brought
              back.

              Default: By default, -import brings only defaults objects

              Data_type: enums={macro special_route pin_constraint}_list

       -nonDefault
              Displays the current non-default settings.

       -quiet Displays  the  current  settings for the specified parameters in
              Tcl list format only.

Example
       The following command reports the value for the -export  parameter  set
       using the set_ptn_fplan_mode command.

       get_ptn_fplan_mode -export

